dct_description_sm: From Netherlands Government charts to 1924 ; published at the Admiralty, 21st, Mar. 1899, under the Superintendence of Rear Admiral Sir W.J.L. Wharton, K.C.B., F.R.S. Hydrographer ; Engraved by Davies & Company ; Sold by J.D. Potter, Agent for the sale of the Admiralty charts ; [U.S. Hydrographic Office] Emergency reproduction of B.A. chart - Oct. 1940.
Depths shown by soundings; relief by form lines and spot heights.
Tidal information chart, 6 profile views, 2 inset charts, longitudinal and latitudinal lines.
Shows low water areas, reefs, waterways, buildings, railways, roads, coal field.
dct_creator_sm: Wharton, W. J. L. (William James Lloyd), 1843-1905
